SBS journalist Scott McIntyre was fired on Sunday over his controversial Anzac day tweets .
The AFR's Geoff Winestock called Anzac Day 'the cultification of an imperialist invasion' and accused Australian Diggers of committing war crimes .
SBS Managing Director Michael Ebeid and Director of Sport Ken Shipp said McIntyre's comments have 'caused his on-air position at SBS to become untenable'